intro: Xanthoxalis europaea f. cymosa, commonly known as the European yellow cinquefoil, is a flowering plant belonging to the family Rosaceae. It is characterized by its bright yellow flowers and compound leaves with five leaflets. The plant typically grows in moist, sandy soils and is native to parts of Europe. It is often found in open habitats such as meadows and woodland edges. Its botanical features make it a notable species for ecological studies and horticultural interest.
